==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Possessory
<hw>Pos*sess"o*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>possessorius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>possessoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of
or pertaining to possession, either as a fact or a right; of the nature
of possession; <as>as, a <ex>possessory</ex> interest; a
<ex>possessory</ex> lord.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Possessory action</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Possessory suit</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an action
to regain or obtain possession of something. See under
<er>Petitory</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Posset</ent>⟦br⟧
